@1245   = ~TWO-HAND STYLE: Investing in this fighting style allows the character to make the best use of two-handed melee weapons, handling them more deftly and inflicting more grievous blows.

Proficient (1 slot): The wielder gets a +1 bonus to thac0 and damage rolls, a -1 bonus to weapon speed factor, and critical hits occur on a roll of 19 or 20 (instead of just 20).

Specialized (2 slots): The wielder's damage bonus increases to +3, and and critical hits occur on a roll of 18 or higher.~
@1246   = ~SHIELD-FIGHTING: By spending slots on this fighting style, a character maximizes the protection afforded by a shield and overcomes the difficulty coordinating the use of both weapon and shield. With further specialization, use of a shield can affect enemies' balance and expose weak points in their defenses.

Proficient (1 slot): The wielder gets a +1 bonus to thac0 and melee AC when using a shield, and a +2 bonus to AC vs. missile attacks

Specialized (2 slots): When struck by a melee attack, there is a 25% chance of performing a Shield Bash, causing that attacker to be knocked back 5 feet and stunned for 2 seconds on a failed save vs. Breath Weapon.~
@1247   = ~FENCING: Investing in this fighting style allows characters to be especially quick and accurate when wielding a single weapon in one hand. 

Proficient (1 slot): The wielder gets a +1 bonus to thac0, AC vs. melee attacks, and weapon speed factor.

Specialized (2 slots): The AC bonus increases to +2 and the wielder's base attack rate is increased to 3 attacks per 2 rounds.~
@1248   = ~proficiencies~
@1249   = ~DUAL-WIELDING: This fighting style involves attacking opponents with two melee weapons at the same time. It is very difficult to coordinate; main-hand attacks suffer from severely decreased accuracy (though opponents often lose track of the character's off-hand weapon, making for a higher chance of a successful strike with it). Without any skill in this style, characters suffer a -4 penalty to thac0 with both the main weapon and the off-hand weapon.

Proficient (1 slot): The thac0 penalties are reduced to -3 with the main weapon and -2 with the off-hand weapon.

Specialized (2 slots): The thac0 penalties are reduced to -2 with the main weapon and no penalty with the off-hand weapon.~
